Thank you for your time.

Also, with Homecoming being moved, we will not be having an early release on Friday, September 25th.

6th Grade and New Student Orientation will be August 4th from 6:00-7:30 p.m.

Drop off begins at 5:45 p.m.
If the student's last name begins with an A - L, please use the bus lot entrance on the backside of the building. The bus lot is accessible from Hart St. These students will go to the gym.
If the student's last name begins with M - Z, they will enter from the main entrance and go to the cafeteria.
At the end of the session, please pick up your child from the entrance that you dropped off.

Vincennes Lincoln Volleyball
July 24 at 10:29 AM ¬∑

‚ùóÔ∏è Attention CMS 7th & 8th Grade Volleyball Players ‚ùóÔ∏è

CMS Volleyball will be hosting 2 open gyms before try outs. These are optional but give you a chance to touch a volleyball. Anyone wanting to try out is welcome to attend.

Location: CMS
Time: 9:00 - 10:30
Dates: August 3 & 4

CMS 7th & 8th grade volleyball tryouts will be on August 10 & 11 from 3:30-5:00pm.

In order to attend workouts, you must self screen before entering the school. If you feel sick or have a temperature over 99.4, PLEASE STAY HOME. You must also bring your own water bottle. Athletes are NOT to use the water fountains. Athletes must also enter and exit the school wearing a mask. During drills a mask is not required.

July 15 from 8-12

The cost is $20. More information will come closer to the date.

VCSC News
April 9 at 9:56 AM ¬∑

Good morning all,

I certainly know that many of you are dealing with larger issues this morning from the storm. It is an E-Learning or counted day for education in the VCSC but this is secondary and quite frankly if it does not occur today, it does not occur.

Many of you are without power and this includes many of our staff members as well and they simply may not be available during the hours of 9AM to 2PM.

As we have learned with Covid-19, we have to be flexible. We just did not know that today that Covid-19 would become secondary for many of us and our attention would turn elsewhere and with this we must be flexible today and patient as we have too many people dealing with much larger issues than that of education and this is primarily related to the storm from last night.

Hopefully we will slowly start to return to what is the new normal for the time being, but today, education is far more secondary.

Hope you all are safe and with this, please stay safe!

Mr. Parsley

post_text:
How do you open a locker?

Tips:
*Turn the knob to the right for your first number.
*Turn it to the left for the second number skipping the number once and stopping on it the second time.
*Turn the knob to the right for your last number.
*Lift up on the latch and your locker will be unlocked.
